From 13aee590af7ccbfa392ffbb49f2eb44a05fc54c4 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Michael Henke <henke.mike@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 15 Jul 2026 15:18:22 -0500
Subject: [PATCH 07/10] fix(task-session-manager): harden session.created net +
 onJobTerminal per review

Address review feedback on #765 session-created-registration-net:

- session.created net: register parent as orchestrator before the
  shouldManageSession check, mirroring tool.execute.before and
  messages.transform. The net exists for the plugin-reload / late-attach
  race, which is exactly when the parent registration hasn't happened yet.
- onJobTerminal: add .catch on the fire-and-forget promptAsync so a
  failed nudge (session gone, provider error) is logged, not silently
  swallowed. Orchestrator still reconciles via idle / transform.
- idleReconcileTimers: move from module scope into the hook factory so a
  plugin re-init cannot fire stale-closure timers on the new instance.
  Only timers carry deferred-execution risk; other module-scoped maps
  are accessed synchronously per event turn.
- notifyJobTerminal helper: collapse the three duplicated
  terminalJobNotified has/add/dispatch blocks (injected completion,
  tool.execute.after, idle reconcile) into one helper so a future call
  site cannot forget the dedup guard.
- phantom cleanup: broaden the guard to also check wasFallbackRecent,
  mirroring the grace-window fix applied to the other suppression sites.
  isFallbackInProgress is cleared by tryFallbackWithAbort's finally
  before the new child's session.created can arrive, so the
  wasFallbackRecent grace window covers the same async gap (#765).
- peek same-ref invariant comment: document that peek/take alias the
  same object and the invariant holds only while no async gap sits
  between them.

All green: typecheck, biome check:ci, 1591 tests.
